OBJECTIVES
BACK
Civil engineering is the cornerstone of the society. It shapes our
cities and towns with variety of landscapes. As it brings so much
advantage for human convenience, it leaves us significant
environmental footprints. It is always known that many construction
models are unsustainable and can threaten our planet. However,
building innovation, builds sustainability. It would create a brighter
future for us.
INTRODUCTION
BACK
There are particular standards and actions that we may do to build our bright future:
1.Resources should be valued, not wasted.
-we can use recycled materials that minimize waste generation and ensures that the
materials were reused at the end of their lifecycle.
2. Building energy-efficient powerhouses.
-optimizing for a building design with natural ventilation, utilizing smart technologies,
reduce energy consumption and carbon emissions.
3. Integrating nature.
-prioritizing green spaces, minimizing impact on ecosystems and preserving
biodiversity.
4. Collaborating partners.
-engineers, architects, builders, and policy makers should share the same vision of
sustainability.
BACK
